 

**STATE OF TEXAS**

**COUNTY OF DALLAS**

**CERTIFICATE OF OWNERSHIP TRANSFER**

**AND CONVEYANCE OF BUSINESS INTEREST**

 

Document No. TH-1910-0314-001

*Executed this Fourteenth Day of March, in the Year of Our Lord Nineteen
Hundred and Ten*

**KNOW ALL MEN BY THESE PRESENTS:**

**WHEREAS,** Robert Edward Hartley, a resident of Dallas County, State
of Texas, hereinafter referred to as the \"Grantor,\" is the lawful
owner of an undivided fifty percent (50%) interest in the business
concern known as **Thoreson & Hartley Toys**, a commercial enterprise
duly organized and operating under the laws of the State of Texas, with
its principal offices and manufacturing facilities located at 412
Commerce Street, Dallas, Texas; and

**WHEREAS,** William Samuel Thoreson, a resident of Dallas County, State
of Texas, hereinafter referred to as the \"Grantee,\" is the present
owner of the remaining fifty percent (50%) interest in said business
concern, and has served as co-proprietor and managing partner since the
incorporation of said enterprise on the Seventeenth Day of June,
Nineteen Hundred and Two; and

**WHEREAS,** the Grantor, acting of his own free will and without
duress, compulsion, or undue influence of any kind, does desire to
transfer, assign, and convey all right, title, and interest in his said
fifty percent (50%) stake in the aforementioned business concern to the
Grantee, in consideration of the Grantee's continued stewardship of the
enterprise and the mutual obligations herein described;

**NOW, THEREFORE, IN CONSIDERATION OF THE PREMISES:**

The Grantor does hereby irrevocably transfer, assign, convey, and set
over unto the Grantee, his heirs, executors, administrators, and
assigns, all of the Grantor's right, title, and interest in and to the
business concern known as Thoreson & Hartley Toys, including but not
limited to: all tangible and intangible assets, inventory, accounts
receivable, goodwill, trade name, customer relationships, manufacturing
equipment, and any and all other property, real or personal, associated
therewith.

The Grantee, upon execution of this instrument, shall become the sole
proprietor and owner of the entirety of the business concern, which
shall hereafter be conducted under such name as the Grantee shall
determine. The Grantee shall assume full authority over all matters
pertaining to the operation, management, and disposition of the
enterprise and its assets.

This transfer is made without reservation, encumbrance, or condition,
and shall be binding upon the parties hereto, their heirs, executors,
administrators, successors, and assigns. This instrument shall be
recorded with the Office of the County Clerk of Dallas County, Texas,
and with the Texas Secretary of State in accordance with applicable
statutes governing the transfer of business interests.

**CONSIDERATION:**

The Grantor acknowledges receipt of good and valuable consideration in
the amount of **One Dollar (\$1.00)** and other considerations, the
receipt and sufficiency of which are hereby acknowledged. No further
compensation, royalty, or continuing interest is retained by the
Grantor.

**IN WITNESS WHEREOF:**

The parties hereto have set their hands and seals on this Fourteenth Day
of March, Nineteen Hundred and Ten, in the City of Dallas, County of
Dallas, State of Texas.

